name: Experiment Or Die #112
description: Project to create a new collage every day for a year using my years of personal assets. I certainly believe that there is a crossroads where the corporate world and the fine art world intersect. Maybe that is where Pop Art resides. Would any piece of art containing a popular icon or logo from the corporate world be considered Pop Art no matter what? I'm not sure it should be. In the end the classification doesn't mean all that much anyway so who cares if it's considered Pop Art or not? Twitter and IG: Nikejerk
